{
  "info": {
    "name": "FileVault API",
    "description": "## FileVault - Secure Cloud File Storage API\n\n**Tech Stack:** Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, Cloudflare R2, JWT Auth\n\n### How to Use:\n1. **Sign Up** → auto-captures verification token (dev mode)\n2. **Verify Email** → paste token from signup response\n3. **Login** → auto-sets `auth_token` for all subsequent requests\n4. **Upload Files** → both anonymous & authenticated flows\n5. **Manage Files** → list, download, share, delete, view stats\n\n### Environment Variables Needed:\n- `base_url` — API base URL (default: `http://localhost:3000`)\n- `auth_token` — auto-populated after login\n- `user_email` / `user_password` — your test credentials\n\n> All authenticated endpoints require `auth_token` to be set in the environment.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
